      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "Notice has been served by the va\nrious plaintiffs in actions brought\nagainst the Great Northern as a re-\nsuit of the Division street freight\nrunaway accident last summer, that\nthe defendant must answer interrog-\natories.\n\n\nThe plaintiffs desire the defendants\nto go on record as to who started the\ncars. in whose custody they were\nat the time they started, who left\nthe cars on the Hillyard switch,\nwhether the brakes were set, whether\na Waterman was in charge. whether\na locomotive had taken other cars\nfrom the switch just prior to their\nstart. whether derailing switches were\nin use; in all, 80 heterogeneous are\nproposed"
    }
  ]
